text.tspan: Use a desoldering tool or copper wick to
remove all solder from the 9 points
Carefully pull the faceplate free from the
rest of the assembly. If necessary, you can
gently flex the chassis to reach a flat tool
under the edge of the faceplate
the reverse order with your new chassis
The backplate should easily separate from the
chassis. If necessary, you can press on the pins
from the front to dislodge it.
Be sure that the face- and backplates are firmly
seated into the chassis while soldering the 9
chassis pins. Using a small spring clamp can help,
but it's sufficient to apply presure with your fingers.
